>> title: Mujadara (Lentils & Rice with Crispy Onions)
>> cuisine: Middle Eastern
>> tags: grain, protein, vegan, gluten-free, soy-free
>> servings: 8
>> yield: 8 cups
>> storage_days: 5
>> storage_method: refrigerated
>> reheat: Microwave with splash of water, covered.

-- This Lebanese classic is pure comfort food - earthy lentils, fluffy rice, and sweet crispy onions.

== Crispy Onions (Start First - 30-40 minutes)

Heat @olive oil{1/3%cup} in #large skillet{} over medium heat.

Add @yellow onions{3%large}(halved and thinly sliced) and @kosher salt{1/2%tsp}. Cook, stirring occasionally, until deeply golden and caramelized, ~{30-40%minutes}. Don't rush!

Set aside half for topping; the other half goes into the lentils.

== Lentils and Rice

While onions cook, rinse @green or brown lentils{1%cup}.

In #large pot{}, combine lentils, @vegetable broth{3%cups}, @ground cumin{1/2%tsp}, @ground cinnamon{1/4%tsp}, @allspice{1/4%tsp}, @black pepper{1/4%tsp}, and @kosher salt{1%tsp}.

Bring to boil, reduce to simmer, cook ~{15%minutes}.

Rinse @long-grain white rice{1%cup} until water runs clear.

Add rice and remaining @vegetable broth{1%cup}. Stir, bring back to simmer, cover, cook ~{15-18%minutes} until rice is tender.

Stir in half the caramelized onions.

== Storage

Fluff with #fork{} and let cool.

Store in #airtight container{}. Top with remaining crispy onions when serving.

-- Serving: Top with fresh parsley, a dollop of coconut yogurt, and extra crispy onions.
